			<h2>Finished Guitar & Work In Progress sections *</h2>
			<hr>
			<section>
				<h5><strong>Create</strong> a new article</h5>
				<p>Visit <a href="https://tinyjpg.com/">this website</a>, it will help you to have your images lower wieght to be uploaded</p>
				<ul>
					<li>You will find this page under <strong>admin</strong> in the navigation menu <%= link_to "Finished Guitars", new_finished_guitar_path  %></li>
					<li>Fill in the title and the description</li>
					<li>In the decription, the text will be formated with the lines breaks and paragraphes</li>
					<li>Click <strong>Add Files</strong></li>
					<li>It will open a window from your computer, then select files</li>
					<li>If you are happy, click <strong>Create 'Finished Guitar'</strong></li>
					<li>If everything is okay you will be redirected to the article you've just created, overwise you will have an error message and pleased to retry.</li>
				</ul>

				<h5><strong>Visit</strong> your articles</h5>
					<ul>
						<li><%= link_to "Page that groups all your Finished Guitars", finished_guitars_path %></li>
						<ul>
							<li>This is where are sorted all you article, the newest the first</li>
							<li>To access article, just click on it</li>
							<li>Images: when you hover an image it gets bigger, and if you click it will open the gallery</li>
							<li>To display the next or previous image, click the little arrows on the side, you can also use your keyboard arrows</li>
							<li>Close the gallery with the white cross on the top right</li>
						</ul>
					</ul>

				<h5><strong>Edit</strong> an existing article</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>Visit an article's page</li>
					<li>Below the images, click on the edit icon <i class="fas fa-edit"></i>
					<li>You can change title and description</li>
					<li>You can remove picture, click on trash icon <i class="fas fa-trash-alt trash"></i></li>
					<li>You can add pictures, click on add pictures</li>
					<li>If you are happy, click <strong>Update Me</strong></li>
					<li>If everything is okay you will be redirected to the article you've just edited, overwise you will have an error message and pleased to retry.</li>
				</ul>

				<h5><strong>Destroy</strong> an existing article</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>Visit an article's page</li>
					<li>Below the images, click on the edit icon <i class="fas fa-edit"></i></li>
					<li>If you are sure, confirm or not ðŸ˜…</li>
				</ul>
				<small> * Finished Guitar and Work In Progress have exactly the same process</small>
			</section>

			<h2>Media</h2>
			<hr>
			<section>
				<h5><strong>Create</strong> a new media</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>You will find this page under <strong>admin</strong> in the navigation menu <%= link_to "Media", new_video_path  %></li>
					<li>Fill in the url form</li>
				 	<li><p>Just go on your youtube profile, open a video and get the link like this one <em>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s0DnPuCGwV8</em>, this special format required</li>
				  <li><p>Mind the little <em>/watch?v=</em> ðŸ¤“</p></li>
				</ul>
				<h5><strong>Edit/Destroy</strong> an existing media</h5>
					<ul>
						<li><%= link_to "Visit the Media page",videos_path  %></li>
						<li>Below each Youtube Frame you have the destroy icon <i class="fas fa-trash-alt trash"></i> and the edit icon <i class="fas fa-edit"></i></li>
					</ul>
			</section>
				
			<h2>Customiaztion</h2>
			<hr>
			<section>
				<h5>Here you become the master!</h5>
				<ul>
				<li>You will find this page under <strong>admin</strong> in the navigation menu <%= link_to "Customiaztion", customization_path  %></li>
				<li>From here you can change almost all</li>
					<ul>
						<li>The main<strong>Background Color</strong></li>
						<li>The <strong>Menu background color</strong></li>
						<li>The <strong>Menu Tags</strong></li>
						<li>The <strong>Primary</strong> color</li>
						<li>The <strong>Secondary</strong> color</li>
						<li>The <strong>Text</strong> (paragraphes) color</li>
						<li>The <strong>Big Titles</strong> color</li>
						<li>The <strong>Cover</strong> image</li>
						<li>The <strong>Work In Progress</strong> section image</li>
						<li>The <strong>Finished Guitar </strong> section image</li>
						<li>The <strong>Media</strong> section image</li>
						<li>The <strong>Avatar</strong> image</li> 
						<li>The <strong>About</strong> description</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
				<h5>Change colors</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>Just select the colors with the color pickers, you will see live change</li>
					<li>You have samples of text and buttons to see what you are changing</li>
				</ul>

				<h5>Change images</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>By default the current used image is diplayed</li>
					<li>Click <strong>Choose file</strong> to add</li>
					<li>A window opens, select just one image</li>
				</ul>

				<h5>Change text</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>Defaut text is in the form</li>
					<li>You can change the text</li>
				</ul>

				<h5>Validate all the change</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>When you are happy and sure, click on <strong>Update Customization</strong></li>
					<li>If you are not, click on <strong>Reset to default layout</strong></li>
				</ul>
			</section>
			<section>
				<h5>Contact form</h5>
				<li>The visitor can send you an email that you will recieve directly on your mail box</li>
				<li>This section is not visible if you are logged in</li>
			</section>
